author: Jeff Seisser | Union sports editor
title: J/C sends seniors out winners
text:
J/C sends seniors out winners Jeff Seisser | Union sports editor Daily Jefferson County Union 
JEFFERSON — The Jefferson/Cambridge High School girls’ swim team sent four seniors out winners, earning a 112-55 non-conference dual win over visiting Lodi on Senior Night Tuesday. 
Seniors Emily Wright, Julia Jensen, Abbey Hay and Bailey Whiting were recognized for their contributions to the program — and all four played a factor in the home-finale victory. 
Wright and Jensen had the biggest send-off, each winning two individual events while being part of two winning relay teams. Wright, Jensen, Whiting and sophomore Parker Fetherston took top honors in the 200-yard medley relay, touching out in 2:06.08. Meanwhile, the same quartet won the 400 freestyle relay in 4:11.43. 
Wright also dominated the freestyle events, winning the 50 free (:26.79) and 100 free (:59.41), while Jensen took top honors in both the 200 freestyle (2:12.50) and 100 backstroke (1:08.56). 
Meanwhile, Whiting earned runner-up honors in both the 200 IM (2:30.83) and 100 backstroke (1:10.40), while Hay was fourth in the 100 freestyle (1:09.41) while being part of the third place 200 medley and 200 freestyle relay teams. 
“We had a lot of PRs, which is good to see,” said Jefferson/Cambridge coach Hannah Peppey. “Hopefully more girls’ times will drop next Tuesday when we face Whitewater.” 
The EagleJays will compete at Whitewater Tuesday. The Southern Lake Conference dual begins at 6 p.m.
